# Resolution 2011-04-13.bg.1: Open64 as associated project

### WHEREAS

1. Open64 is a substantial and useful open source project.

2. Open64 would like SPI's support and assistance, including taking
   donations.

### THE SPI BOARD RESOLVES THAT

1. Open64 is formally invited to become an SPI Associated Project,
   according to the SPI Framework for Associated Projects, SPI Resolution
   1998-11-16.iwj.1-amended-2004-08-10.iwj.1, a copy of which can be found at
   [http://www.spi-inc.org/corporate/resolutions/2004/2004-08-10.iwj.1](/corporate/resolutions/2004/2004-08-10.iwj.1/)

2. The Open64 Steering Group acting by consensus resolution is
   recognized as the authoritative decision maker for Open64, and
   Aida Rivas is recognized by SPI as the current designated liaison
   for Open64.

3. This invitation will lapse, if not accepted by the Open64 Steering
   Group, 60 days after it is approved by the SPI Board.

